==English==
===Etymology===
'''Guru''', from Sanskrit meaning heavy. An etymology based on the Advayataraka [[Upanishad]] (14--18, verse 5) describes the syllables gu=darkness and ru=dispeller, as in '''dispeller of darkness'''.

===Noun===
'''guru''' 
#A Hindu spiritual teacher.
#An advisor or mentor.
#:''He acted as her guru, giving much needed advice over the years.''
#A leader or expert in a field.
#:''The Wiktionary guru made many helpful contributions.''
